libfprint uses the Meson build system. See
http://mesonbuild.com/Quick-guide.html for details on how to
compile libfprint.

The "meson configure" command will give you a list of available
command-line options.


------

Install dependencies for Ubuntu:

sudo pip3 install ninja meson
sudo apt install cmake build-essential libglib2.0-dev libgusb-dev \
  libcairo2-dev libgirepository1.0-dev libnss3-dev libgudev-1.0-dev \
  gtk-doc-tools valgrind

